                            jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            jcr:title="Important Day 1 Activities"
                            sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/title/v2/title"
                            type="h2"
                            variant="h"/>
                        <text
                            cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                            jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-23T11:25:03.843-05:00"
                            jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                            jcr:lastModified="{Date}2023-01-24T17:34:55.737-05:00"
                            jcr:lastModifiedBy="chiucx"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                            text="&lt;p>We understand there are a lot of things to take care of as you start your new career at AbbVie. Below is a short list of what you should act on as soon as you have appropriate system access.&amp;nbsp;&lt;b>PLEASE NOTE:&amp;nbsp; The two-step I-9 process legally MUST be completed within 3 days of your employment start date by meeting with an authorized I-9 representative.&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                            textIsRich="true"/>
                        <accordion_copy
                            cq:styleIds="[1,8]"
                            jcr:created="{Date}2022-12-22T18:39:04.465-05:00"
                            jcr:createdBy="chiucx"
                            jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-04-14T16:45:32.362-04:00"
                            jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                            jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                            sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/accordion/v2/accordion"
                            headingElement="h6"
                            singleExpansion="false">
                            <item_1671753835763
                                cq:panelTitle="Critical Form I-9 Process"
                                cq:styleIds="[1659545825678,1659545847147]"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-01-29T15:13:17.711-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="stromkx1"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                text="&lt;p>&lt;b>&lt;span class=&quot;body-unica-20-reg&quot;>On-Site I-9 Completion Instructions:&lt;/span>&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;If you are located in the below locations:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Worcester, MA&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Branchburg, NJ&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>Waco, TX&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>This is a two-step process:&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;b>Step 1&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Before your first day, complete Section 1 at: &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newi9.com&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>www.newi9.com&lt;/a> using the &lt;b>AbbVie employer code 15101.&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;b>Step 2&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Meet with an HR Representative on-site to present your original unexpired &lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/joinus/acceptable-documents.pdf&quot;>acceptable document(s)&lt;/a> on or shortly after your first day of employment to complete Section 2. Additional instructions will be sent to your personal e-mail soon*. A copy of your documents will also be required.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;If you are experiencing COVID symptoms, have been in direct contact with someone diagnosed or experiencing symptoms, or have been diagnosed with COVID, or other reasons, please respond to the email regarding your I-9 appointment.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;span class=&quot;body-unica-14-reg&quot;>*Notify &lt;a href=&quot;mailto:HRConnect@abbvie.com&quot;>HRConnect@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;if you will not be within 50 miles of your work location during your first week. You may then follow the All-Others instructions below to complete your I-9.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-unica-20-reg&quot;>All Others I-9 Completion Instructions&lt;/span>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Begin this process immediately&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;Complete your I-9 through an&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://hrx.talx.com/ec/#/login/15101/Template/09091054-06ae-4116-be2d-a59719dc7b33&quot;>Equifax service called&amp;nbsp;I-9 Anywhere&lt;/a>, which offers remote Form&amp;nbsp;I-9&amp;nbsp;Section 2 completion through authorized&amp;nbsp;I-9&amp;nbsp;representatives near you.&amp;nbsp;&lt;b>Appointments fill up fast and completing the Form I-9 in advance of your start date will ensure you meet the&amp;nbsp;&lt;i>critical&lt;/i>&amp;nbsp;federal deadline no later than three days from your start date.&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>This is a two-step process:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Step 1: Go to&amp;nbsp;&lt;b>&lt;a href=&quot;https://hrx.talx.com/ec/#/login/15101/Template/09091054-06ae-4116-be2d-a59719dc7b33&quot;>I-9 Anywhere&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;now&lt;/b>&amp;nbsp;and&amp;nbsp;select your&amp;nbsp;AbbVie work location or Virtual&amp;nbsp;(from the drop-down list) to complete Section 1.&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>Step 2: Follow the on-screen instructions to make your appointment to present your documents to complete Section 2.&amp;nbsp;You must present your original, unexpired,&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/joinus/acceptable-documents.pdf&quot;>acceptable document(s)&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;during your in-person I-9 verification.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                            <item_1671752892401
                                cq:panelTitle="Still Have I-9 Questions?"
                                cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-02-10T11:56:19.121-05:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                text="&lt;p>&lt;b>I-9 Process:&amp;nbsp; Frequently Asked Questions&lt;/b>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>1. I completed the first section of the I9 process and received the confirmation code. What else do I need to do? Who should I be scheduling an appointment with to present my documents?&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>If you are a virtual new hire or an employee not located at Worcester, Branchburg or Waco, complete section 1 of your&amp;nbsp;I9 at:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://hrx.talx.com/ec/#/login/15101/Template/09091054-06ae-4116-be2d-a59719dc7b33&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>I9-Anywhere&lt;/a>. Follow the on-screen instructions to make your appointment to present your documents to complete Section 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>If you are a new hire located at Worcester, Branchburg or Waco, you will be contacted by an HR representative&amp;nbsp;to schedule your appointment to present your documents. Before your first day, complete section 1 of your I9 at:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.newi9.com/&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>https://www.newi9.com/&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;using the AbbVie employer code 15101&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>2. I am out of town/traveling or will not relocate to my work location until after my start date. What can I do?&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>If you are not located at Worcester, Branchburg or Waco within the first 3 days of your start date, complete section 1 of your I9 at:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;https://nam12.safelinks.protection.outlook.com/?url=https%3A%2F%2Fhrx.talx.com%2Fec%2F%23%2Flogin%2F15101%2FTemplate%2F09091054-06ae-4116-be2d-a59719dc7b33&amp;amp;data=05%7C01%7Camy.neurauter%40abbvie.com%7C8a3d23a2a200452a3b6108da378df34c%7C6f4d03de95514ba1a25bdce6f5ab7ace%7C0%7C0%7C637883380048263839%7CUnknown%7CTWFpbGZsb3d8eyJWIjoiMC4wLjAwMDAiLCJQIjoiV2luMzIiLCJBTiI6Ik1haWwiLCJXVCI6Mn0%3D%7C3000%7C%7C%7C&amp;amp;sdata=ryOT7kA3B1xGAiJQULjLVVsf01YjGvMiNNhkqs%2BQY6E%3D&amp;amp;reserved=0&quot;>I9-Anywhere&lt;/a>. Follow the on-screen instructions to make your appointment to present your documents to complete&amp;nbsp;Section&amp;nbsp;2.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>3. I am located in a different state and will move to my AbbVie work location in the future. What address should I use for the physical address in section 1 of the I9 Form?&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>You can use your current address, the address in section 1 will not trigger any changes on the process.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;b>4. I completed my I-9 through I-9 Anywhere. Is there anything else I need to do?&lt;/b>&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ul>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>If you have completed your I-9 through I-9 Anywhere and presented your documentation, thank you - no further action is required. You will be contacted by HRConnect if there are any issues or follow-up required.&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;i>&lt;br>&#xd;&#xa; &lt;/i>For additional I-9 questions, send an e-mail to:&amp;nbsp;&lt;a href=&quot;mailto:HRConnect@abbvie.com&quot;>HRConnect@abbvie.com&lt;/a>&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ul>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                            <item_1671812736259
                                cq:panelTitle="Review the Total Rewards Recording, Resources Guide and New Hire Checklist"
                                cq:styleIds="[1659545825678]"
                                jcr:lastModified="{Date}2026-04-14T16:49:25.843-04:00"
                                jcr:lastModifiedBy="VALENSX5"
                                jcr:primaryType="nt:unstructured"
                                sling:resourceType="abbvie-com2/components/text/v2/text"
                                langAttribute="none"
                                text="&lt;p>Selecting benefits that match your needs is a personal decision and comes with a lot to consider. Start learning about our benefits and programs before your first day using the following resources:&lt;/p>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;ol>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;a href=&quot;https://bcove.video/4tBfBr5&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>U.S. Total Rewards Dual Enrollment recorded video (36:12)&lt;/a> – This video provides an overview of all benefits and programs. It also shows how we make HR information easier to find, understand and use through AI.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/joinus/2026-abv-total-rewards-resources-guide-jan-publish.pdf&quot;>U.S. Total Rewards Resources Guide&lt;/a> –This document provides additional details on our benefits and programs and is great for quick reference.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;li>&lt;a href=&quot;/content/dam/abbvie-com2/pdfs/joinus/abbvie-new-hire-checklist.pdf&quot;>New Hire Benefits Checklist&lt;/a> – Simply your benefits onboarding by following this time-bound checklist. Once you gain access to AbbVie’s network, use the AI prompts on the second page to dig deeper into our benefits, programs, company policies and more.&lt;/li>&#xd;&#xa;&lt;/ol>&#xd;&#xa;"
                                textIsRich="true"/>
                        </accordion_copy>
                    </container_58189511>
